gle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 03, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lrm1665702891992.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lrm1665702891992.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lrm1665702891992.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lrm1665702891992\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Uniface COM Configuration Utility\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the Uniface COM Configuration utility to configure the COM connector or create COM definitions for specific applications.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lrm1665702891992__section_w5775ab1b7b1_w5776ab1b7_w5777ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d195397e55\">\n                 \n How to\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lrm1665702891992__li_d18158e1_d18159e1_d18160e1\">To start the utility, choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">COM Configuration</span> from the Uniface group in the Windows <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Start</span> menu, or run <span class=\"ph filepath\">ucomcfg.exe</span>.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lrm1665702891992__li_d18161e1_d18162e1_d18163e1\">To configure the COM connector, set the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Global Uniface COM settings</span>. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cgr1665702879587.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cgr1665702879587.html\" title=\"The COM connector provides full COM connectivity for Uniface applications.\">Configuring the COM Connector</a>.\n                  </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lrm1665702891992__li_d18164e1_d18165e1_d18166e1\">To create a COM configuration definition: <ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lrm1665702891992__li_d18167e1_d18168e1_d18169e1\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">New</span> and\n                     provide a name for the definition. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lrm1665702891992__li_d18170e1_d18171e1_d18172e1\">Set the values for the configuration files\n                     and directories required by the application. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lrm1665702891992__li_d18173e1_d18174e1_d18175e1\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span> or\n                        <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Apply</span> to save the definition. </li>\n</ol>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lrm1665702891992__p_d35423e1_d35424e1_d35425e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jdj1665702753782.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jdj1665702753782.html\" title=\"For a COM client to use Uniface services it needs to know the components’ interface definitions. These are contained in a standard Microsoft Windows type library, which is contained in a standard Microsoft Windows self-registering DLL. The type library DLL must be installed on the client workstation and the client’s Registry settings must point to the server workstation.\">Enabling COM Call-In</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"roz1665702891854.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/roz1665702891854.html\" title=\"For COM clients to locate and load an object, you need to register the object’s class in the Microsoft Windows Registry.\">Registering Type Libraries</a>. </p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lrm1665702891992__section_w5778ab1b7b3_w5779ab1b7_w5780ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d195397e130\">\n                 \n Fields\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lrm1665702891992__li_d18176e1_d18177e1_d18178e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"enq1665702892061.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/enq1665702892061.html\" title=\"Create and edit configuration definitions for specific applications.\">Configuration Definitions</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lrm1665702891992__li_d18179e1_d18180e1_d18181e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hig1665702753988.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hig1665702753988.html\" title=\"Specify the files and directories required by the Uniface application that COM connector needs to access.\">Settings for Selected Configuration Definition</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"lrm1665702891992__li_d18182e1_d18183e1_d18184e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xsz1665702892138.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xsz1665702892138.html\" title=\"Specify global options for the COM connector.\">Global Uniface COM Settings</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529700\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529700\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface COM Configuration Utility Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 03, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface COM Configuration Utility Use the Uniface COM Configuration utility to configure the COM connector or create COM definitions for specific applications. How to To start the utility, choose COM Configuration from the Uniface group in the Windows Start menu, or run ucomcfg.exe . To configure the COM connector, set the Global Uniface COM settings . For more information, see Configuring the COM Connector . To create a COM configuration definition: Click New and provide a name for the definition. Set the values for the configuration files and directories required by the application. Click OK or Apply to save the definition. For more information, see Enabling COM Call-In and Registering Type Libraries . Fields Configuration Definitions Settings for Selected Configuration Definition Global Uniface COM Settings Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}